28/03/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Interior Minister Rumen Petkov met with Montenegrin counterpart Jusuf Kalamperovic on Tuesday (March 27th) in Sofia. They agreed that the fight against drug trafficking and illegal immigration is a top priority, as is regional co-operation. Petkov also offered Bulgaria's help regarding EU-related reforms. 
Also Tuesday, the British Defence Manufacturers Association and the Association of Bulgarian Defence Industry Enterprises sealed a memorandum of understating regarding co-operation in the sector. Deputy Defence Minister Simeon Nikolov explained the agreement would connect Bulgarian businesses with the world's leading military technology producers. (News.bg, Focus, MINA - 27/03/07)
